<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This maps a return value or argument to any MaybeLive return values or</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// arguments it uses. This allows the MaybeLive values to be marked live</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// when any of its users is marked live.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example (indices are left out for clarity):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Uses&#91;ret F&#93; = ret G</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00097" /><CodeLine lineNumber="97"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    This means that F calls G, and F returns the value returned by G.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Uses&#91;arg F&#93; = ret G</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    This means that some function calls G and passes its result as an</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    argument to F.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Uses&#91;ret F&#93; = arg F</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    This means that F returns one of its own arguments.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Uses&#91;arg F&#93; = arg G</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00104" /><CodeLine lineNumber="104"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    This means that G calls F and passes one of its own (G&#39;s) arguments</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="105"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    directly to F.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00106" /><CodeLine lineNumber="106" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#afb15aeeba5e11ad17b03524730d51b7d"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#a9cbc5f82a665596b0ff5d374dcf9d01c">UseMap</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#afb15aeeba5e11ad17b03524730d51b7d">Uses</a>;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00107" /><CodeLine lineNumber="107"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="108" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#adccc69f6d0152bec28db15a70cf05587"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">using </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#adccc69f6d0152bec28db15a70cf05587">LiveSet</a> = std::set&lt;RetOrArg&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00109" /><CodeLine lineNumber="109" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#a1eb5a2eac80c369977d7c8747be838ba"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">using </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/deadargumenteliminationpass/#a1eb5a2eac80c369977d7c8747be838ba">LiveFuncSet</a> = std::set&lt;const Function &#42;&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
